attributeList.attribute: Binding is not affected by a change in pH from 7.5 to 5.8.
norpA will bind to the PDZ5 domain of inad but with a Kd=30uM. The oxidation of PDZ45 abolished its binding to the norpA peptide
Derived from pupal ovarian tissue of the fall armyworm
Cloned from the parent cell line, IPLB-SF-21-AE (SF-21)

Wild type Inad was not phosphorylated by ePKC, however substitution of Thr669 with Ala, a mutation originally designed to mimic non-phosphorylated state of the residue, led to dramatically increased phosphorylation. Thr513Ala in the PDZ45 interface also led to an increase of its phosphorylation
